    "question_id": "Q4",
    "framework": "AFME",
    "text": "Has your regulator raised any material issues in respect of your banking, custody and client money activities within the last 12 months?"
  },
  "outbound_response": "BNY and its subsidiaries are routinely named as defendants in or made parties to pending and potential legal actions in the ordinary course of business [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-25-000118::PART_II.Item_6#0168]. The firm is also subject to governmental and regulatory examinations, information-gathering requests, investigations and proceedings, both formal and informal, and claims for significant monetary damages are often asserted in many of these legal actions, while claims for disgorgement, restitution, penalties and/or other remedial actions or sanctions may be sought in governmental and regulatory matters [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-24-000133::PART_II.Item_6#0174]. It is inherently difficult to predict the eventual outcomes of such matters given their complexity and the particular facts and circumstances at issue in each matter; however, on the basis of current knowledge and understanding, BNY does not believe that judgments, settlements or orders, if any, arising from these matters \u2014 either individually or in the aggregate, after giving effect to applicable reserves and insurance coverage \u2014 will have a material adverse effect [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-24-000133::PART_II.Item_6#0174]. As of March 31, 2026, BNY did not record any material liabilities under its clearing and settlement exchange sponsorship arrangements [span:edgar:bny-mellon-corp:0001390777-26-000060::PART_II.Item_6#0145].",
